				"string" : "# ‚úî SOM reference vectors: what they are\n\nIn SOM:\n\n* each neuron holds a **reference vector** (weight vector)\n* through repeated interaction with data\n* the neuron‚Äôs internal model gradually becomes a **prototype** of a region of the input space\n* neighboring neurons maintain **coherent internal models** through the neighborhood function\n* this yields a **structured map of internalized input regularities**\n\nThis is precisely why the SOM is often interpreted as:\n\n> *‚Äúa perceptual sheet of internalized expectations.‚Äù*\n\nThat is **exactly Br√•ten-like**.\n"
