				"string" : "# ‚úî Mapping SOM ‚Üí Br√•ten‚Äôs ‚Äúparticipatory mirror-matching‚Äù\n\n| Br√•ten                       | SOM                                                        |\n| ---------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Internal model of the Other  | Reference vector m·µ¢                                        |\n| Participatory updating       | Neuron updates through BMU + neighborhood interaction      |\n| Embodied coupling            | Neighborhood function h·µ¢‚±º(t) couples units during learning |\n| Coherent relational topology | SOM grid (2D lattice) maintains adjacency relations        |\n| Emergence of shared meaning  | Smoothly ordered feature map                               |\n\nIn short:\n\n### ‚úî Each reference vector is a *mirror* of a region of the input world.\n\n### ‚úî Neighboring reference vectors are *co-mirrors* that coordinate through learning.\n\n### ‚úî The whole map becomes an *internalized topology* of the external world.\n\nThis is deeply Br√•ten-esque.\n"
